I was able to get shell output, running commands with phpseclib. It&#39;s a bit more tricky but allows you to execute commands under another user (and also in another server if needed).

 - create user with rights to run your jar
 - create public/private key pair to that user
give read access to your webserver to user&#39;s private key (that&#39;s why you don&#39;t want to use your personal user account)
 - install phpseclib: add something like &lt;code&gt;&quot;phpseclib/phpseclib&quot;: &quot;~2.0&quot;&lt;/code&gt; to your
   **composer.json** and make **composer update** or use some other way to make it available to your code

&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code&gt;
